displayName: House of Senator Pilia, Painting Room

parameters:
Elder Council Member Pilia: It's an impressive number of
paintings, isn't it? They're not my personal taste, but
rather all my father's taste.

Elder Council Member Pilia: I may be the curator of this art
museum, but even at my age, I still can't fully understand
the value of art.
Clea: May I ask you about your troubles?

Elder Council Member Pilia: Here is a painting called
'Portrait of a Young Girl,' which was once displayed here
and was most beloved by my father.

Elder Council Member Pilia: However, this painting was
boldly stolen, with a threatening letter sent beforehand,
bypassing all security measures.

Elder Council Member Pilia: The one who stole it is the
Phantom Thief Perno.

Elder Council Member Pilia: And recently, a threatening
letter arrived here with the message 'Shouldn't the runaway
girl return to the mansion?'

Clea: If we take the message literally, does it mean we have
to come here to return the paintings?

Mage Relm: I can't trust that! They might come to steal
other paintings!

Elder Council Member Pilia: It might be a prank, but just to
be safe, I would appreciate it if you could provide
security.

Maid Amina: Once I am ready, please let me know so that I
can assist with the security as well.

Elder Councilor Pilia: A runaway girl... quite an ironic
choice of words, isn't it?

events.name: 放蕩貴族からの依頼並列

parameters:
Maid Amina: There is a possibility of a battle. Are you
really prepared?
Clea: No problem, I can go anytime.

Maid Amina: Then let's wait. It seems that the guards of
Kanonas will also come as reinforcements.

Maid Amina: Why do you become an adventurer? Your behavior
makes me feel your good upbringing.

Maid Amina: Why do you go out of your way to take dangerous
paths?

Clea: I joined the Adventurer's Guild for my own sake, to
avenge my parents.
Clea: It's okay if you don't believe me.
Kanonas Guard: W-What's this? Something feels off...!?
Clea: Everyone, please be on guard!

Maid Amina: Ugh... This is... Ahh... I'm getting... so
sleepy... Ahh...
Clea: What is this... What on earth...
Hehehe, next it's your turn... Shall we go?
Clea: Where is Perno...!? Ouch, it hurts!

Priestess Sophia: You mustn't move yet, Clea-san. You've
just had your wounds treated, after all.

Mage Relm: It's completely ridiculous! Clea-san, please take
a look!
Clea: The painting... it was just like the warning letter.

Elder Council Member Pilia: I can't believe it's actually
being returned... I don't understand it, but can I be happy
about it?

Elder Council Member Pilia: You've even gotten injured for
my sake. Let me pay you a reward in place of Lloyd.

Elder Council Member Pilia: There was a letter from the
thief Perno to you, placed in front of the returned
painting.

Clea: To someone as dedicated to their work as to harm
themselves, I will someday entrust you with a request when
you have recovered.

Thief Nora: A-Are you going to make me help with the
theft...? I'm scared...
Mage Relm: Are you saying that as a thief...?

Elder Council Member Pilia: Regardless, I am grateful for
your efforts in bringing back the painting.

Maid Amina: I apologize for not being of any help. I would
appreciate it if you could come to the mansion for a report
to the master.
Maid Amina: Please take care of me.
